\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The desert was not only vast: there was intimacy in its involutions and granularity- the cool mouth of a tunnel dug by a mouse; the arc scribed by a windblown strand of vegetation; the campfires dome of light. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The sands,\u8221\'94 wrote Thomas, \u8220\'93are a public diary\u8230\'85 No bird may alight, no wild beast or insect pass but needs must leave its history.\u8221\'94}
